Implement: $ARGUMENTS

## Before You Code (MANDATORY)

1. Read @memory/INDEX.md (global overview)
2. Read @memory/conventions.md (project patterns)
3. Read @memory/workflows/api/insights.md (API learnings)
4. Read @memory/workflows/api/gotchas.md (API traps)
5. Read @memory/workflows/api/test-flows.md (existing test commands)

## Loop (strict order, no skipping)

1. **Plan**: Outline API endpoint.
   - HTTP method and path
   - Request/response schema
   - Auth requirements
   - Rate limiting needs

2. **Code**: Implement following conventions.md.
   - Route handler
   - Input validation (Zod/Joi/etc.)
   - Error handling
   - Response formatting

3. **Unit Test**: Delegate `@agents/tester`.
   - Test handler logic
   - FAIL → fix, re-run. Max 3 attempts.

4. **Integration**: Run integration tests.
   - Full HTTP request/response
   - Auth flows if protected
   - Same fix loop.

5. **Review**: Delegate `@agents/reviewer`.
   - API design review
   - Address findings.

## After Shipping (MANDATORY)

1. Update @memory/workflows/api/insights.md (what learned)
2. Update @memory/workflows/api/gotchas.md (new traps found)
3. Update @memory/workflows/api/test-flows.md (new test commands)
4. Create @memory/decisions/api/{{date}}-slug.md (ADR if significant)
5. If global insight → append to @memory/INDEX.md
6. **Report**: Summarize shipped, decisions, insights captured.

## API Checklist

- [ ] Input validated
- [ ] Errors return proper status codes
- [ ] Response follows API conventions
- [ ] Documented in API spec (if applicable)
